1) DEFINITIONS
--------------
“Software” means the SarahMemory Project source code, binaries, documentation,
comments, configuration files, schemas, protocols, APIs, user interfaces,
workflows, updates, patches, mods, plugins, extensions, build artifacts, and
all associated materials.

“Non-Commercial Use” means use by an individual person, hobbyist, researcher,
non-profit, or community group where the Software is not used primarily to
generate revenue and is not used by or on behalf of a commercial entity.

“Corporate / Commercial Use” means use by, for, or on behalf of:
- any corporation, company, LLC, partnership, or other commercial entity;
- any government agency using the Software for commercial procurement or
  contracted operations;
- any paid product, paid service, subscription, or revenue-generating business
  process (including internal business systems);
- any managed, hosted, SaaS, consulting, or outsourced service involving the
  Software.

“Corporate License” means a paid license agreement issued by the Licensor that
permits Corporate / Commercial Use.

“AI / ML System” means any artificial intelligence system, machine learning
model, neural network, foundation model, large language model, multimodal
model, autonomous agent, or automated decision system.

“Deploy” means to run, host, expose, embed, or make the Software available to
any third party or system by any means.

“Restricted Entities” are defined in Section 9.


