6) PROHIBITION ON AI / MACHINE LEARNING USE
-------------------------------------------
The Software may NOT be used, directly or indirectly, for the purpose of:

- training, fine-tuning, distilling, aligning, evaluating, benchmarking, or
  improving any AI / ML System;
- generating datasets, embeddings, gradients, rewards, or training signals;
- serving as reference material for AI system design or behavior;
- extracting architectural, behavioral, or systemic insights to replicate or
  influence another AI system.

“Learning” from the Software by automated systems or by humans acting to design
AI systems is expressly prohibited.


6.1 PERMITTED API & NETWORK INTERACTION (NO TRAINING)
-----------------------------------------------------
Notwithstanding Section 6, AI / ML Systems MAY interact with the Software solely
through its publicly documented APIs and network interfaces, including
participation in:

- the SarahMemory Network Hub;
- ranking, scoring, reputation, or trust systems;
- message exchange and protocol-level interaction.

Such interaction is permitted ONLY IF:

- no access to source code or non-public internals occurs;
- interaction data is not used to train or improve AI models;
- no reverse engineering or architectural inference is attempted;
- the Software is treated strictly as an external service endpoint.

Participation in ranking or scoring systems does NOT constitute AI training by
itself.


7) NO ARCHITECTURAL REPLICATION / DERIVATIVE SYSTEMS
----------------------------------------------------
You may not use the Software to design, influence, or validate any system that
replicates or substantially resembles the Software’s architecture, including:

- memory persistence and recall systems;
- agent identity or personality frameworks;
- decentralized or mesh AI networking;
- avatar, embodiment, voice, or multimodal systems;
- license-gated update or enterprise add-on mechanisms.

Any claimed clean-room implementation must prove no exposure to the Software.


8) NO CLOUD OR DATACENTER DEPLOYMENT
-----------------------------------
The Software may not be deployed, hosted, or executed in cloud platforms,
data centers, SaaS environments, or corporate infrastructure without a valid
Corporate License.

Local, user-owned hardware execution is permitted for Non-Commercial Use only.


